main event: Two civilians reported seeing an unidentified flying object near California, Missouri on January 30, 1967.
interesting points: The object had lights that were cycling very fast in colors of white, green, red, and bright blue.
The object was observed moving up and down at varying rates of speed, and went over the farm before turning northwest and flying over the town of California, Missouri.
The witnesses stated the motion was too slow for a plane and too fast for a helicopter.
No sound was reported from the object.
A front was moving into the area at the time, causing dense fog by 3:00 AM.
sighted object: a bright, multi-colored object with rapidly cycling lights
